(Unimplemented, Overflow, Ambiguous, etc.)\n- Provides contextual error messages based on the obligation cause\n- Suggests potential fixes (importing traits, fixing type annotations, etc.)\n- Reports related trait implementations that almost matched\n\n### 7. New Trait Solver Integration\n**Files:**\n- `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/solve/fulfill.rs` - New FulfillmentCtxt\n- `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/solve/fulfill/derive_errors.rs` - Error derivation\n- `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/solve/select.rs` - Selection in new solver\n\nThe newer trait solver provides an alternative implementation with improved performance and correctness. The `FulfillmentCtxt` in solve/fulfill.rs uses the next-gen solver engine from `rustc_next_trait_solver`. The `fulfillment_error_for_no_solution()` and `fulfillment_error_for_stalled()` functions in derive_errors.rs generate appropriate error codes from solver results, including detection of higher-ranked trait bound violations and projection mismatches.\n\n### The Complete Chain:\n\n1. **ObligationForest** (`rustc_data_structures`) - stores obligation tree structure\n2. **FulfillmentContext** (`rustc_trait_selection/fulfill.rs`) - manages overall fulfillment\n3. **FulfillProcessor** - processes obligations through the forest\n4. **SelectionContext** (`rustc_trait_selection/select/mod.rs`) - driven by FulfillProcessor\n5. **assemble_candidates()** - collects candidate implementations\n6. **assemble_candidates_from_impls()** - searches trait impl database  \n7. **MatchAgainstFreshVars** - performs pattern matching on impl signatures\n8. **confirm_candidate()** - validates selected candidate through unification\n9. **report_selection_error()** - reports errors for unsatisfied bounds\n\nFor the newer solver path, the chain is:\n1. **FulfillmentCtxt** (solve/fulfill.rs) - new solver's fulfillment\n2. **SolverDelegate** - bridges to the core solver\n3. **fulfillment_error_for_no_solution()** - derives errors from solver results\n\nThis design enables efficient trait resolution with good error messages while supporting both incremental obligation processing and complete error recovery."
